# Architecture

## Data model (`src/types.ts`)

```ts
type LngLat = [number, number];
type LngLatEle = [number, number, number?];

interface Waypoint { id: string; pos: LngLat; name?: string }

interface Leg {
  fromId: string; toId: string;
  coords: LngLatEle[];          // routed polyline (incl. elevation)
  distanceM: number; ascentM: number; descentM: number;
  profile: string;
  status: 'pending' | 'ok' | 'error' | 'straight';
}

interface Route {
  id: string; name: string;
  waypoints: Waypoint[];
  legs: Leg[];                   // legs[i] connects waypoints[i] -> waypoints[i+1]
  profile: BrouterProfile;
  createdAt: number; updatedAt: number;
}
```

**Invariant**: `legs.length === Math.max(0, waypoints.length - 1)`. `legs[i]` always connects `waypoints[i]` to `waypoints[i+1]`.

## Per-leg routing — the central pattern

A "leg" is the routed segment between two consecutive waypoints. **Always re-fetch only the legs that touch a changed waypoint** — do NOT re-route the whole polyline:

| Edit | Affected legs |
|---|---|
| Insert waypoint at index `i` | `legs[i-1]` and `legs[i]` (newly inserted) |
| Drag/move waypoint at index `i` | `legs[i-1]` and `legs[i]` |
| Delete waypoint at index `i` | The two adjacent legs collapse into one new leg |
| Profile change | All legs (re-fetched in order) |

Implemented in `src/state/routeStore.ts` (`rerouteAround`, `addWaypoint`, `removeWaypoint`). When a leg is being fetched, set `status: 'pending'` so the map renders it dashed; on network error, fall back to a straight line with `status: 'straight'`.

Deletion must update `waypoints` and `legs` atomically in the same Zustand `set`. In particular, deleting down to fewer than two waypoints must set `legs: []` in that same write; otherwise MapLibre can briefly keep rendering stale route-source geometry until the next route update.

## File layout

```
src/
  App.tsx                  # composition root, wires file/save logic + keyboard shortcuts
  main.tsx                 # bootstrap (StrictMode + maplibre css import)
  components/
    MapView.tsx            # MapLibre map, markers, route source/layers, gestures
    Toolbar.tsx            # top floating toolbar (file ops, mode, undo, profile)
    RoutePanel.tsx         # bottom sheet — name, stats, elevation, waypoint list
    ElevationProfile.tsx   # SVG chart sampled from leg coords
    WaypointList.tsx
    LibraryDrawer.tsx      # IndexedDB-backed library
    InstallHint.tsx        # one-shot iOS A2HS hint
  state/
    routeStore.ts          # zustand store: waypoints, legs, profile, undo/redo, file/library bindings
  services/
    brouter.ts             # routeLeg() — single leg via BRouter, in-memory cache
    gpx.ts                 # parseGpx, serializeGpx (GPX 1.1 + runmapper:* extension)
    fsAccess.ts            # FS Access API + download/upload fallback
    idb.ts                 # listRoutes, loadRoute, saveRoute, renameRoute, deleteRoute
  hooks/useInstallHint.ts
  types.ts
  global.d.ts              # FS Access API typings (not yet in lib.dom)
  styles.css               # Tailwind base + maplibre tweaks + marker classes
```

## How MapView talks to the store

`MapView` mounts the MapLibre map once, then **subscribes to the store imperatively** (`useRouteStore.subscribe(selector, listener, { equalityFn, fireImmediately })`). The listener mutates MapLibre marker positions and updates the GeoJSON source directly — React never re-renders the map. This is intentional: do not refactor MapView to redeclare markers on every render.

## Selection model

`useRouteStore.selectedIds: string[]` (multi-select). `length === 1` is the typical single-selected case. Actions:

| Action | Effect |
|---|---|
| `setSelected(id \| null)` | Replace selection with `[id]` (or `[]` when null). Used for marker clicks / WaypointList taps in non-Pencil-select modes. |
| `toggleSelected(id)` | Add or remove one id. Used by Pencil-select mode tap-on-marker. |
| `setSelectedIds(ids[])` | Bulk replace. Used after a Pencil-select rect/lasso drag releases. |
| `clearSelection()` | `[]`. Also called automatically by `setPencilMode(m)` whenever `m !== "select"`. |
| `removeWaypoints(ids[])` | Bulk delete with one history snapshot, then re-route remaining legs in order. |

The Delete-selected button in the Toolbar's Route menu calls `removeWaypoints(selectedIds)` and shows a count badge when `selectedIds.length > 1`.

## Pencil event flow

Pencil interactions live on `map.getCanvas()` via raw `pointerdown/move/up/cancel`, filtered by `pointerType === "pen"`. We `e.preventDefault()` to suppress synthesized touch events (otherwise MapLibre would interpret a Pencil drag as a touch pan). During active Pencil strokes in Add/Select modes, `MapView` also temporarily disables `map.dragPan` and restores its previous state on release/cancel. See `.cursor/rules/ipad-ux.mdc` "Pencil modes" for full details.

The existing finger handlers (`map.on("click", ...)`, the long-press `touchstart`) early-return when `pencilMode !== "off"` so finger never adds while Pencil mode is engaged.
